ve far-ﬁeld sites that would help to reconcile the LGM ice volumes estimated from GIA studies and those estimated from summing regional ice sheet reconstructions, the impact is nonetheless large enough that GIA analyses of RSL records in the far ﬁeld of ice sheets should include 3-D viscoelastic Earth models.},
	language = {en},
